1.) What is FIND_IN_SET() in MySQL?

FIND_IN_SET(str, strlist) â†’ checks if a string is present inside a comma-separated list.
Returns the position (1-based index) if found.
Returns 0 if not found.
Returns NULL if any argument is NULL.

example ::
select find_in_set('apple', 'apple,orange,mango');   -- returns 1
select find_in_set('mango', 'apple,orange,mango');   -- returns 3
select find_in_set('grapes', 'apple,orange,mango');  -- returns 0
select 
    person_name,
    case when find_in_set('apple', fruits_name) > 0 then 'Yes' else 'No' end as Apple,
    case when find_in_set('orange', fruits_name) > 0 then 'Yes' else 'No' end as Orange
from basket;


2.) IF(condition, value_if_true, value_if_false)
select 
    name,
    if(score >= 90, 'Excellent', 'Not Excellent') as performance
from students;
